All examples are symmetric at the antidiagonal, that is

  M[i,j] = M[N-1-j, N-1-i] .

Further observations (all indices 0-based):

1. Row i is strictly decreasing from column i+1 on, and also strictly decreasing
   on the initial part, except for the last row.
2. The first row has k (N=12 -> k=5) strictly above the average, starting from index 1,
   and that block moves right with going to the next row, falling off at
   the end.
